title: FillStrata
text: First set test data 5 strata Next run optimal allocation Tables strata sample sizes total sample 30, 100 300. Total variance total sample size 300 Sample size ensures total variance larger 1000 Total sample size 200 chosen advance Total sample size 250 minimum 40 stratum Total sample size 300 minimum 40 first two strata 50 others. Total sample size 250 maximum 70 stratum Total sample size 250 maximum 30 first two strata 100 last three
code: s2       <- c(35, 3, 2, 30, 7)         # Variance estimate N        <- c(100, 100, 500, 50, 150)  # N in each strata names(N) <- paste("st",1:5,sep="")  # Strata-names totY     <- c(8800,900,5500,400,300)   # Totals in each strata g        <- c("grA","grA","grB","grB","grB") # Two groups a = FillStrata(s2, N) table(a$filledStrata[1:30]) ##  ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##   8   2  10   4   6 table(a$filledStrata[1:100]) ##  ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  28   8  33  13  18 table(a$filledStrata[1:300]) ##  ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  83  24  99  38  56 a$sumVar[300] ## [1] 7953.557 table(a$filledStrata[1:(max(which(a$sumVar >= 1000)) + 1)]) ##  ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ## 100  66 271  50 150 table(FillStrata(s2, N, totn = 200)$filledStrata) ##  ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  55  16  66  26  37 table(FillStrata(s2, N, totn = 250, min_n = 40)$filledStrata) ##  ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  59  40  71  40  40 table(FillStrata(s2, N, totn = 300, min_n = c(40, 40, 50, 50, 50))$filledStrata) ##  ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  73  40  87  50  50 table(FillStrata(s2, N, totn = 250, max_n = 70)$filledStrata) ##  ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  70  22  70  36  52 table(FillStrata(s2, N, totn = 250, max_n = c(30, 30, 100, 100, 100))$filledStrata) ##  ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  30  25 100  39  56

title: FillStrata
text: following example using FSmatrix total sample size 200 chosen advance. 3 ways allocating n strata Alternativ functions: Allocation using varLimits Alternatives: Calculate CV totY strata known allocation (20%) Alternatives CV group: Allocation CV: 2% 3% two groups Alternatives: Allocation , totYgroup intput instead totY Allocation CV groups overall previous example totnGroup new input earlier example min_nGroup new input
code: m = FSmatrix(s2=s2, N=N, totn=200, group=g) m[,1]$n ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  55  16  66  26  37 m[1,]$Strata ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  55  16  66  26  37 m[[1,1]] ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  55  16  66  26  37 FillStrata(s2=s2,N=N,totn=200,group=g,returnMatrix=TRUE)[[1,1]] ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  55  16  66  26  37 FillStrata(s2=s2,N=N,totn=200,group=g,returnTable=TRUE) ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  55  16  66  26  37 FStotnAlloc(s2=s2,N=N,totn=200,group=g) ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  55  16  66  26  37 vL = c(5000,10000)   # variance limits for groups  m = FSmatrix(s2=s2,N=N,varLimits=vL,group=g) m[[1,1]] # Allocated n in each strata ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  52  15  72  28  41 m[3,] # Total variance in strata, group (less than limits) and all. ## $Strata ##      st1      st2      st3      st4      st5  ## 3230.769 1700.000 5944.444 1178.571 2791.463  ##  ## $Group ##      grA      grB  ## 4930.769 9914.479  ##  ## $All ##      all  ## 14845.25 FillStrata(s2=s2,N=N,varLimits=vL,group=g,returnMatrix=TRUE)[[1,1]] ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  52  15  72  28  41 FillStrata(s2=s2,N=N,varLimits=vL,group=g) ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  52  15  72  28  41 FSvarAlloc(s2=s2,N=N,varLimits=vL,group=g) ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  52  15  72  28  41 m = FSmatrix(s2=s2,N=N,totY=totY,max_n=round(N/5),group=g) m[5,] # CV in strata, group and all. ## $Strata ##       st1       st2       st3       st4       st5  ##  1.344564  3.849002  1.149919 19.364917 21.602469  ##  ## $Group ##      grA      grB  ## 1.271013 1.921996  ##  ## $All ##      all  ## 1.078392 FSmatrix(s2=s2,N=N,totY=totY,min_n=round(N/5),group=g,cvLimits=Inf)[[5,2]] ##      grA      grB  ## 1.271013 1.921996 FillStrata(s2=s2,N=N,totY=totY,min_n=round(N/5),group=g,cvLimits=Inf) ##      grA      grB  ## 1.271013 1.921996 FillStrata(s2=s2,N=N,totY=totY,min_n=round(N/5),group=g,cvLimits=Inf,returnMatrix=TRUE)[[5,2]] ##      grA      grB  ## 1.271013 1.921996 FStotCV(s2=s2,N=N,totY=totY,min_n=round(N/5),group=g) ##      grA      grB  ## 1.271013 1.921996 m=FSmatrix(s2=s2,N=N,totY=totY,cvLimits=c(2,3),group=g) m[[1,1]] # Allocated n in each strata ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  12   3  26  10  14 m[5,] # CV in strata, group (less than limits) and all. ## $Strata ##       st1       st2       st3       st4       st5  ##  1.820548 10.943175  2.454934 19.364917 33.665016  ##  ## $Group ##      grA      grB  ## 1.938766 2.992827  ##  ## $All ##      all  ## 1.661585 FillStrata(s2=s2,N=N,totY=totY,cvLimits=c(2,3),group=g,returnMatrix=TRUE)[[1,1]] ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  12   3  26  10  14 FillStrata(s2=s2,N=N,totY=totY,cvLimits=c(2,3),group=g) ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  12   3  26  10  14 FScvAlloc(s2=s2,N=N,totY=totY,cvLimits=c(2,3),group=g) ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  12   3  26  10  14 FSmatrix(s2=s2,N=N,totYgroup=c(10000,5000),cvLimits=c(2,3),group=g)[[1,1]] ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  11   3  37  15  21 # Alternatives FillStrata(s2=s2,N=N,totYgroup=c(10000,5000),cvLimits=c(2,3),group=g,returnMatrix=TRUE)[[1,1]] ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  11   3  37  15  21 FillStrata(s2=s2,N=N,totYgroup=c(10000,5000),cvLimits=c(2,3),group=g) ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  11   3  37  15  21 FScvAlloc2(s2=s2,N=N,totYgroup=c(10000,5000),cvLimits=c(2,3),group=g) ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  11   3  37  15  21 g2 = cbind(struktuR:::makeDummy(g),1) # Create dummy matrix from g and add extra column colnames(g2)[3] = "All" # In Ex4 overall CV is 1.66. Now we set 1.6 as overall limit in addition to "2" and "3"  m=FSmatrix(s2=s2,N=N,totY=totY,cvLimits=c(2,3,1.6),group=g2) FSmatrix(s2=s2,N=N,totYgroup=c(10000,5000),cvLimits=c(2,3),group=g,totnGroup=c(10,100))[[1,1]] ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##   8   2  37  15  21 # Group 1: Results changed so that total is 10. Group 2 below 100 -> no change FSmatrix(s2=s2,N=N,totYgroup=c(10000,5000),cvLimits=c(2,3),group=g,min_nGroup=c(10,100))[[1,1]] ## st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  ##  11   3  51  20  29 # Change in group 2 since below 100

title: Calculation of sigma squared — CalcS2
text: Calculation sigma squared using either residual simple variance level, difference ratio statistics. function includes options averaging several periods.

title: Calculation of sigma squared — CalcS2
code: CalcS2(   data,   yVar,   xVar = NULL,   strataVar,   sampleVar = NULL,   residVariance = TRUE,   baseVar = NULL,   estimateType = list("level", "diff", "ratio"),   meanType = c("y", "var"),   p = 1,   printPlot = FALSE )

title: Calculation of sigma squared — CalcS2
text: data dataset yVar variable name interest variable (y). Eg "turnover" xVar name activity variable relates interest variable. Eg "numberOfEmployees" strataVar variable used stratification sampleVar variable used identify companies included sample. used cases interest variable (y variable) available population. variable specified , y-values sample used calculate s2. Default NULL residVariance Whether calculate residual variance. Default residual. baseVar Variable provides values fixed base difference ratio statistics. missing, moving base used previous period. estimateType type statistic calculated. Choose beteen "level" standard level statistic, "diff" difference statistic, "ratio" = ratio statistic. provided, function defaults level statistic. meanType case several periods data, meanType specifies averaged. Default "var" calculated sigma sq takes average. "y" takes average y values first calculates sigma sq. p Specifies much overlap periods difference ratio statistic. Default p = 1 indicates full overlap periods. printPlot Indicates whether print boxplots residual values (ei ai) identify outliers. One plot made period difference/ratio period. Default FALSE.

title: Optimal allocation of sample sizes — FSmatrix
text: s2 estimate variance within strata. example s2 = c(35, 3, 2, 30, 7) N population size within strata. example N = c(100, 100, 500, 50, 150) totn total desired sample size varLimits desired maximum variance group.  Note: varLimits given, different output value returned - sample size fulfills required group variance totVar.  varLimits = Inf, output group sum totVar "n = min_n". group vector dummy matrix giving groups used varLimits totY Estimate total Y stratum. cvLimits desired maximum CV group. can single value vector values. totYgroup Estimate total Y group. Alternative instead totY. min_n minimum sample size stratum. can single number used strata vector numbers (one stratum). totVar function calculating total variance s2, n (sample size) N inputs.  function able handle vectors inputs give vector output. nullcorrection Variance n=0 set nullcorrection times variance n=1. large value needed algorithm (Inf). use_n Matrix number columns strata. column contain desired sample size choices (accept missing values) corrSumVar Logical value giving corrected variance used. Default FALSE. dotprint Condition invoke printing "---------#--------...." calculations. Default set totn > 1000. intern Logical value giving function used internally within another function . Default set FALSE. max_n maximum sample size stratum. can single number used strata vector numbers (one stratum). groupNames Alternative instead finding group names input. returnGroupN Logical whether return population group size. returnGroupn Logical whether return sample group size. returnTable Logical whether return table returnTotYgroup Logical whether return total Y values returnVarLimits Logical whether return  Y limits returnMulti Logical whether return multi returnMatrix Logical whether return matrix totnGroup Maximal total sample size within group (override cvLimits) min_nGroup Minimal total sample size within group (override cvLimits)

text: output FSmatrix (FillStrata returnMatrix=TRUE) two-dimensional list. Column:Strata Output values according strata. Column:Group Output values according group specified input. Column:Output treating strata single group. Row:n Allocated sample size Row:N Population size Row:totVar Total variance Row:totY Total Y Row:cv CV (%) Row:varLimits input (Group) Row:cvLimits input computed varLimits (Group) output FillStrata list two elements varLimits cvLimits used. filledstrata Strata filled sequentially according vector. sumVar Total variance values total n. returnTable=TRUE varLimits cvLimits used (FStotnAlloc, FSvarAlloc, FScvAlloc, FScvAlloc2) output allocated sample size strata. elements FSmatrix-output can obtained setting return-parameters TRUE using varLimits=Inf cvLimits=Inf.

title: Optimal allocation of sample sizes — FSmatrix
code: # Examples with 5 strata based on FSmatrix   s2    = c(35, 3, 2, 30, 7)         # Variance estimate   N     = c(100, 100, 500, 50, 150)  # N in each strata   names(N) = paste("st",1:5,sep="")  # Strata-names   totY  = c(8800,900,5500,400,300)   # Totals in each strata   g     = c("grA","grA","grB","grB","grB") # Two groups   # Total sample size of 200 chosen in advance   m = FSmatrix(s2=s2,N=N,totn=200,group=g)   # Three ways of getting allocated n in each strata   m[,1]$n #> st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  #>  55  16  66  26  37    m[1,]$Strata #> st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  #>  55  16  66  26  37    m[[1,1]] #> st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  #>  55  16  66  26  37     # Alloc from varLimits   vL = c(5000,10000)   # variance limits for groups    m = FSmatrix(s2=s2,N=N,varLimits=vL,group=g)   m[[1,1]] # Allocated n in each strata #> st1 st2 st3 st4 st5  #>  52  15  72  28  41    m[3,] # Total variance in strata, group (less than limits) and all. #> $Strata #>      st1      st2      st3      st4      st5  #> 3230.769 1700.000 5944.444 1178.571 2791.463  #>  #> $Group #>      grA      grB  #> 4930.769 9914.479  #>  #> $All #>      all  #> 14845.25  #>     #  Calculate CV from totY in strata from known allocation (20%)   m = FSmatrix(s2=s2,N=N,totY=totY,max_n=round(N/5),group=g)   m[5,] # CV in strata, group and all. #> $Strata #>       st1       st2       st3       st4       st5  #>  1.344564  3.849002  1.149919 19.364917 21.602469  #>  #> $Group #>      grA      grB  #> 1.271013 1.921996  #>  #> $All #>      all  #> 1.078392  #>
